Dr. '''Muhammad Machasin''' is a professor of history of Islamic culture at the State Islamic University (UIN) Sunan Kalijaga in [[Yogyakarta]], [[Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.transnational.org/SAJT/forum/meet/2006/Rossi_Machasin.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-01-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100708000643/http://www.transnational.org/SAJT/forum/meet/2006/Rossi_Machasin.html |archivedate=2010-07-08 |df= }}</ref> as well as a director of the Islamic Higher Education in Indonesia <ref>[http://www.globethics.net/web/guest/actual-newsletter;jsessionid=8D9CACBF1FE7637C34AAB290B1D0389A]{{dead link|date=May 2018}}</ref>
He has been actively promoting interfaith dialogue and is a member of the board of the [[Asian Council on Religion and Peace]].

