'''Robert F. Barkowski''' (born 29 March 1963 in [[Zielona Góra]]) is a Polish writer, author of history books in Polish<ref>[http://katalogi.bn.org.pl/iii/encore/search/C__Srobert%20f.%20barkowski__Orightresult__U?lang=pol&suite=cobalt Katalog Biblioteki Narodowej BN]</ref> and German.<ref>[https://portal.dnb.de/opac.htm?query=%22barkowski%22+AND+%22robert%22+AND+%22f.%22&method=simpleSearch&cqlMode=true German National Library DNB]</ref> He spent his childhood, school years, early university years and first employment in [[Gdańsk]]. Since the late 1980s he has been living in [[Berlin]]. His works are mainly focused on history of Europe in the Middle Ages.
Cooperation's with German publishing houses (Stroemfeld Verlag, Parthas Verlag,<ref>[http://www.parthasverlag.de/robert-f-barkowski.html Author info by publisher]</ref> [[Form und Zweck|form+zweck]], viceversaverlag, [[Deutscher Kunstverlag]], vorwärts buch) as an author, editor, translator and publisher, as well as Polish publishing house [[Bellona Publishing House|Bellona]] as an author.
For years he is engaged in promoting Polish literature, culture and knowledge about Poland in Germany. On 11 May 2016 he received the medal of honour "For Merits for Polish Culture" by the minister of culture and education.{{Citation needed|date=January 2017}}
